1. *Platiš* karticom ili gotovinom? (Do you pay with a card or in cash?)
2. Ja *platim* račune na vreme. (I pay my bills on time.)
3. Kada *platiš* dugove, osećaš se lakše. (When you pay off your debts, you feel relieved.)
4. Oni *plate* visoku cenu za kvalitetnu hranu. (They pay a high price for quality food.)
5. Nije fer da samo ti *platiš* kaznu. (It's not fair that only you pay the fine.)
6. *Plaćanje* računa je obaveza svakog građanina. (Paying bills is every citizen's obligation.)
7. Molim vas da mi *platiš* ovu uslugu unapred. (Please pay for this service in advance.)
8. *Platiš* li ti članarinu za teretanu? (Do you pay your gym membership fee?)
9. Kada si mi *platio* dug, zaboravio si kamatu. (When you paid me back the debt, you forgot about the interest.)
10. *Plaćam* kafu, ti platiš sok. (I'll pay for the coffee, you pay for the juice.)

Note: In Serbian, "platiš" can be translated to "pay", "you pay" or "to pay". It can also appear in different forms such as "platim", "plate" and "platio" depending on the tense and person.